					const containerName = 'map_canvas_desktop';

						style: 'https://map1.whatismyipaddress.com/styles/liberty',
						center: radiusCenter,
						zoom: 6,
						maxZoom: 6,
						container: containerName,
						attributionControl: false,
						dragPan: false,
						dragRoate: false,
						touchZoomRotate: false,
					});
					
					const nav = new maplibregl.NavigationControl({ showCompass: false });
					map.addControl(nav, 'top-left');
					
					const popup = new maplibregl.Popup({anchor: 'bottom', offset: 10, closeButton: false, closeOnClick: false});
					popup.setHTML('<a href="https://whatismyipaddress.com/ip/158.220.78.10" style="text-decoration:none;outline:none;">Click for more details about <b>158.220.78.10</b></a>');
					popup.setMaxWidth("300px");
					
					const marker = new maplibregl.Marker({color:'red', scale:0.5});
					marker.setLngLat(radiusCenter);
					marker.setOffset([0,0]);
					marker.setPopup(popup);
					marker.addTo(map);
					marker.togglePopup();

					map.on('load', () => {
						document.getElementById('map_attribution').innerHTML = '<div class="maplibregl-ctrl maplibregl-ctrl-attrib"><div class="maplibregl-ctrl-attrib-inner" style="font-size:9px; line-height: 16px;">&copy; <a href="https://openmaptiles.org/">OpenMapTiles</a> | <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright" target="_blank">OpenStreetMap</a></div></div>';

				<script type="text/javascript">
					document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
						var param_id = "ipv6";var param_text = "Checking...";						document.getElementById(param_id).innerHTML = param_text;
						var delay=2000; //1 second
						setTimeout(function() {
							DScheck();
						}, delay);
					}, false);

					function DScheck() 
					{
						var param_id = "ipv6";var param_v = 6;var param_token = "655ad5f2c018712a9f66490c6d4dded2";				
						var xhr=false;
						if (window.XMLHttpRequest) {
							// code for IE7+, Firefox, Chrome, Opera, Safari, SeaMonkey
							xhr=new XMLHttpRequest();
						} else {
							// code for IE6, IE5
							xhr=new ActiveXObject("Microsoft.XMLHTTP");
						}
						if (xhr==false) {
							document.getElementById(param_id).innerHTML = 'None';
						} else {
							xhr.onreadystatechange=function() {
								if (xhr.readyState === 4) {
									varContent = 'Check failed';
									if (xhr.status >= 200 && xhr.status < 300) {
										const json = (function(response) {
											try {
												return JSON.parse(response);
											} catch (err) {
												return undefined;
											}
										})(xhr.responseText);
										if ((json !== undefined) && json.hasOwnProperty('data') && json.data.hasOwnProperty('ipv'+param_v)) {
											const ip = json.data['ipv'+param_v];
											if (ip == '') {
												varContent = "Not detected";
											} else {
												const expression = /^[0-9A-Fa-f.:]+$/;
												if (expression.test(ip)) {
													varContent = "<a href='/ip/"+ip+"' style='color:#fff;'>"+ip+"</a>";
												}
											}
										}
									}
									document.getElementById(param_id).innerHTML = varContent;
								}
							}
				
							xhr.open("GET", 'https://whatismyipaddress.com/api/ds3?token=655ad5f2c018712a9f66490c6d4dded2&v='+param_v, true);
							xhr.setRequestHeader("Accept", "application/json");
							xhr.send();
						}
					}		
				</script>

						<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
					
						<h3>Whats my IP address?</h3>
						<p>Wondering "how can I check my IP?" You're not alone. Your IP address is a unique number linked to your online activity, somewhat like a return address on a letter. </p>
						<p>Whether you're checking emails, shopping, or chatting online, your IP address works tirelessly behind the scenes. It's assigned by your Internet Service Provider (ISP), allowing you to connect to the Internet through a network, whether at home, work, or on the go. Your IP address can change, especially when you switch networks while traveling. If you’re curious to know what is my IP, scroll to the top of the page to see your digits! </p>
						<p>Check out our <a href="https://whatismyipaddress.com/learning">blog</a> to learn more about how IP addresses work, their importance, and how to manage your online presence effectively.</p>
						<p>Also, be sure to read our <a href="https://whatismyipaddress.com/ip-basics">IP 101: The Basics of IP Addresses</a>.</p>
					
						<h3>What is a public IP address?</h3>
						<p>A public IP address is a unique numerical label assigned to each device connected to the Internet, allowing for the identification and communication between devices on a global scale. </p>
						<p>Think of it as your digital home address that enables you to send and receive data over the Internet. This address is assigned by your Internet Service Provider (ISP) and is visible to the wider Internet, distinguishing your device from the billions of others connected worldwide.</p>
					
						<h3>How does my public IP address affect me?</h3>
						<p>Your public IP address plays a crucial role in your online experience. It is essential for:</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Online Communication:</strong> It allows you to access websites, send emails, and connect to various online services by directing the data you request back to your device.</li>
							<li><strong>Security and Privacy:</strong> Understanding your public IP can help you take measures to protect your online privacy and security, as it can be used to determine your general IP location and potentially other personal information.</li>
							<li><strong>Remote Access and Online Gaming:</strong> A public IP address enables you to set up remote access to your home network, participate in online gaming, and use VoIP services more efficiently.</li>
							<li><strong>Website Hosting:</strong> If you're hosting a website or server, your public IP address allows users from around the globe to find and connect to your site or service.</li>
						</ul>
						<p>It's important to note that while your public IP address is essential for Internet connectivity, it can also pose privacy and security risks. Using <a href="https://whatismyipaddress.com/hide-ip">VPNs</a> or proxy services can help mask your public IP address from the public eye, enhancing your online privacy.</p>
					
						<h3>How do I show my IP address?</h3>
						<p>Finding or showing your IP address is a simple process that can be done in a few steps, depending on the device you are using. Your IP address, which stands for Internet Protocol address, is your unique identifier on the internet. Here's how you can find it:</p>
						<p>Via Our Website: For the quickest and easiest way, visit our website and use our tool that automatically displays your current public IP address at the top of the homepage. This method does not require any technical knowledge and works for any device connected to the internet.</p>
						<p>Remember, your public IP address can reveal information about your location and Internet Service Provider (ISP). If privacy is a concern, consider using a <a href="https://whatismyipaddress.com/internet-privacy-is-hard-to-come-by-unless-you-use-a-vpn">VPN</a> or proxy service to mask your IP address.</p>
					
						<h3>Should I change my IP address?</h3>
						<p>Changing your IP address can be beneficial for several reasons:</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Enhanced Privacy and Anonymity:</strong> By changing your IP address, your online activities become hidden from third parties, including websites, cybercriminals, and even your Internet Service Provider (ISP). This ensures that your browsing, streaming, and gaming remain private.</li>
							<li><strong>Dedicated IP Benefits:</strong> Obtaining a Dedicated IP can streamline your online interactions. You'll face fewer dreaded CAPTCHAs, enjoy secure access to business servers and online payments, and maintain a consistent virtual location in select countries. This is particularly advantageous for those requiring stable access for work or personal use.</li>
							<li><strong>Comprehensive Online Protection:</strong> Utilizing services like <a href="https://ho-app.cyberghostvpn.com/aff_c?offer_id=133&amp;aff_id=1985&amp;source=homepage_en">CyberGhost</a>, <a href="https://go.expressvpn.com/c/314904/1481166/16063?subId1=homepage_en">ExpressVPN</a>, <a href="https://go.nordvpn.net/aff_c?aff_id=732&amp;offer_id=15&amp;url_id=902&amp;source=homepage_en">NordVPN</a>, <a href="https://ho-app.kape.com/aff_c?offer_id=1855&amp;aff_id=7876&amp;source=homepage_en">Private Internet Access</a>, &amp; <a href="https://affiliate.ipvanish.com/aff_c?offer_id=19&amp;aff_id=1977&amp;source=homepage_en">IPVanish</a> not only changes your IP address but also shields you from other online threats. Enjoy a cleaner browsing experience without intrusive ads and trackers, improved performance, and enhanced security against cyber threats.</li>
							<li><strong>Concealed Location:</strong> A changed IP address masks your physical location by connecting you to a private, encrypted VPN server. This level of privacy ensures that not even your ISP can monitor your online activities, offering peace of mind and additional security.</li>
							<li><strong>Secure Public Wi-Fi Use:</strong> Changing your IP address through a VPN provides a secure and private connection, even on unsecured public Wi-Fi networks. This allows you to safely browse, shop, and bank on the go without risking your personal information.</li>
						</ul>
						<p>In summary, changing your IP address through a reliable VPN service can significantly improve your online security, privacy, and convenience.</p>
